Create a feature request in Linear and optionally start work immediately.

## Usage

```
/feature-linear
/feature-linear <brief description>
```

## Description

Quick shortcut for creating feature requests without template selection. This command automatically uses the "Feature" template for new functionality.

Perfect for:
- New features and capabilities
- New user-facing functionality
- New API endpoints or integrations
- New pages or workflows
- Significant new additions to the product

## Workflow

### Step 1: Feature Description

Claude asks:
```
Would you like to add context, or should I draft the feature?

Options:
1. I'll provide context (you describe it)
2. Draft it for me (Claude creates comprehensive feature description)
```

**Option 1 - You provide context:**
Claude prompts you for:
- Title
- Feature description (what it does)
- User story (who needs it and why)
- Acceptance criteria (when it's done)
- Technical notes (implementation considerations)
- Design/mockups (if applicable)

**Option 2 - Claude drafts:**
Claude analyzes your request and creates:
```markdown
## Feature Description
[What this feature does and why it matters]

## User Story
As a [user type], I want to [action] so that [benefit].

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] [Criterion 1]
- [ ] [Criterion 2]
- [ ] [Criterion 3]
- [ ] [Criterion 4]

## Technical Notes
[Implementation approach, architecture considerations, dependencies]

## Design/Mockups
[Placeholder for designs or link to figma]

## Out of Scope
[What this feature does NOT include]
```

### Step 2: Issue Created
```
Feature created: {{formats.issueExample}} - [Title]

Linear URL: https://linear.app/{{linear.workspaceName}}/issue/{{formats.issueExample}}
```

### Step 3: Start Work (Optional)
```
Ready to start building this feature? (Y/n)
```

If you say yes, Claude follows the normal workflow:
1. Fetches feature details from Linear
2. Creates comprehensive task analysis
3. **Asks for confirmation before posting to Linear:**
   ```
   Task analysis complete!

   Would you like me to post a summary comment to Linear? (Y/n)
   ```
4. **If yes:** Build comment summary from task analysis, then post to Linear
5. **If no:** Skip building and posting entirely, continue with workflow
6. Creates feature branch
7. Makes initial commit

